commitResults.messageTitle: Initial chatbot: Rename chatbot and add initial messages
commitResults.messageBody:
For customisation, change the name of the chatbot from "Duke"
to "BingBong". Add starting and ending messages for this
preliminary bot.

commitResults.messageTitle: Echo: Add echo capabilities to the bot
commitResults.messageBody:
Allow the bot to repeat the command provided in the user's input,
until the "bye" command is issued for termination.

For proper formatting of the horizontal lines, there is no longer
a need for the GoodbyeMessage class, so remove it.

commitResults.messageTitle: Task tracking: Add ability to track tasks in storage
commitResults.messageBody:
Use an array to remember the tasks in the user input.
If task storage exceeds the limit, throw an exception.

commitResults.messageTitle: Formatting: Change name of static variables to upper-case

commitResults.messageBody:
- Abstract the handling of task records in a TaskTracker class.
- Add boolean attribute to a Task, so as to keep track of its
progress.
- Handle different commands in BingBong class.

commitResults.messageBody:
- Add input for test cases in input.txt

commitResults.messageTitle: Exception handling: Add mechanisms to handle invalid inputs
commitResults.messageBody:
Handle the following exceptions, whilst accounting for whitespaces
in the input:
- Missing fields
- Invalid commands
- Invalid fields (eg. non-parseable indices
for mark and unmark commands)
- Invalid indices for mark and unmark commands

fix: Correct the loading of tasks from .txt file
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, the TaskTracker was made to be immutable. However,
the loading of tasks did not account for this immutability,
meaning that the tasks were not properly read from the text file.
This led to an empty tracker, even if there was an
existing text file.

Fix this by first populating a mutable ArrayList with the
loaded tasks, before passing it into a constructor of
TaskTracker.

feat: Add assertions to check for incorrect state
commitResults.messageBody:
Add assertions within BingBong.java, Parser.java,
TaskTracker.java and MainWindow.java to check for the presence
of invalid states during the running of the program.

- BingBong.java: Check whether or not certain class attributes have
not been initialised, and are still null.
- Parser.java: Check whether or not the mapping of command
types to command functions has not been populated.
- TaskTracker.java: Check whether or not the number of tasks in
the task list is invalid, after certain operations (eg. less than
or equal to 0, after an addition of a task).
- MainWindow.java: Check whether or not image streams are null.

commitResults.messageBody:

and merely describe how the code is being written. Also refactor the
setupMapping() method in Parser, where each lambda expression now
corresponds to a separate private static method.
